  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Arabic Edition of Water as a Human Right</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="FR"></narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The IDRC-published book, Water as a Human Right (eds. A.K. Biswas, E. Rached and C. Tortajada), has garnered considerable attention in the Middle East and North Africa. For example, two of the editors were invited to give a major talk at the Nobel Conference in October 2009. Translating the book into Arabic would increase its reach and maximize its impact. This grant will cover the cost of translating, editing, printing and disseminating the Arabic edition of the book, Water as a Human Right, as well as its launch in Egypt or during the Fifth World Water Forum in Istanbul (2009).</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="FR"></narrative>
  </description>
